==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impedimenta
<hw>Im*ped`i*men"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.
See <er>Impediment</er>, <er>Impede</er>.]</ety> <def>Things which
impede or hinder progress; incumbrances; baggage;</def>
<specif>specif.</specif> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>, <def>the supply trains which
must accompany an army.</def></p>

<p><q>On the plains they will have horses dragging travoises, dogs with
travoises, women and children loaded with <qex>impedimenta</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Julian Ralph.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impedimental</ent>⟦br⟧
